Chile Approves Copec’s Coal Project in Isla Riesco, El Mercurio Reports

-- B y   J o s e   E n r i q u e   A r r i o j a
-- 
2011-08-13T15:18:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-13/chile-approves-copec-s-coal-project-in-isla-riesco-el-mercurio-reports.html
Chile ’s government approved the
first phase of coal mining project in Isla Riesco, newspaper  El
Mercurio  reported on its online edition, citing Environment
Minister, Maria Ignacia Benitez.  The project in the Magellan region will be developed by
 Empresas Copec SA (COPEC) , Chile’s largest pulp exporter, and Grupo
Ultramar, a maritime services provider, aims to invest $530
million.   Isla Riesco’s coal project will supply its production to
power plants in the center and north region of the country, El
Mercurio reported.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jose Enrique Arrioja at 
 jarrioja@bloomberg.net  